
|WKBSYNTAX
======|YKB
tell <player> <message>
tell <player1,player2,player3> <message>

|WKBDESCRIPTION
===========

|YKOThe |YKB'tell' |YKOcommand sends a message to the specified player, if that
player is currently logged on the mud.  Additionally, that player's
reply-to will be set to your name.

|YKBreply <message>|YKO

The |YKB'reply' |YKOcommand sends a message to the last player who sent you
a message via |YKB'tell'|YKO, if that player is currently logged on the mud.

|YKBreplyto <player>|YKO

The |YKB'replyto' |YKOcommand sets the name of the player to which the |YKB'reply'|YKO
command will send a message. The |YKB'tell' |YKOand |YKB'reply' |YKOcommands automatically
set this for you, so use |YKB'replyto' |YKOonly if you wish to manually set it.
